# SUB QUERY : 
-- A query written inside another query is known as sub query.
-- OUTER QUERY | I/P |  <======================= | O/P | INNER QUERY

# EXECUTION PRINCIPLE :
-- Lets consider two queries outer query and inner query.
-- Inner query executes first.
-- Inner qury executes first generates output and its given as a input to the outer query.
-- Outer qury executes after the completing execution of inner query and generate result.
-- Therefore we can state that outer query is dependent on inner query.
-- This is the execution principle of sub-query.

# CASE 1 :
-- Whenever we have unknown present/value or indirect condition in the given question then we go for sub query.
EXA : Diaplay details of empl having 8k sal.  --> Here having sal > 8k direct condition is given
      WAQTD details of empl earning sal same as smith sal --> smiths sal indirect condition/Unknown value

1. WAQTD details of empl having sal same as smiths sal.
--> SELECT * 
    FROM EMP
    WHERE SAL > (SELECT SAL
                 FROM EMP
                 WHERE ENAME = 'SMITH');     
2. WAQTD name and sal of emps earning sal more than james and less than ford.
--> SELECT NAME, SAL
    FROM EMP
    WHERE SAL > ( SELECT SAL 
                  FROM EMP
                  WHERE ENAME = 'JAMES') AND
          SAL < ( SELECT SAL
                  FROM EMP
                  WHERE ENAME ='FORD');

3. WAQTD empls having job same as allen and ward.
--> SELECT *
    FROM EMP 
    WHERE JOB IN ( SELECT JOB
                   FROM EMP
                   WHERE ENAME IN ('ALLEN','WARD'));

4.WAQTD name and deptno of empls from each dept if there are 3 ampls working in it.
--> SELECT ENAME,DEPTNO 
    FROM EMP
    WHERE DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO
                      FROM EMP
                      GROUP BY DEPTNO
                      HAVING COUNT(*) > 3 );

5. WAQTD name ,sal and deptno of empls having max sal from each dept.
--> SELECT ENAME, SAL, DEPTNO
    FROM EMP
    WHERE SAL IN ( SELECT MAX(SAL)
                   FROM EMP
                   GROUP BY DEPTNO );

# CASE 2 :
-- Whenever data to be selected and condition to be executed are from different tables then we go for sub query.
EXA : display empl details whose job loc is yew work
-- here empl details are in emp table and the condition that shoud be executed is from dept table

1. WAQTD dname of allen.
--> SELECT DNAME
    FROM DEPT
    WHERE DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO
                      FROM EMP
                      WHERE ENAME IN 'ALLEN' );

2. WAQTD name of the empls working in new york along with deptno.
--> SELECT ENAME, DEPTNO
    FROM EMP
    WHERE DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO
                      FROM DEPT
                      WHERE LOC = 'NEW YORK' );

3. WAQTD details of empls having max sal and working in new york.
--> SELECT * 
    FROM EMP
    WHERE SAL = ( SELECT MAX(SAL)
                  FROM EMP ) AND
          DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO 
                      FROM DEPT
                      WHERE LOC = 'NEW YORK' );

4.WAQTD ename, sal and deptno of empl getting max sal from chicago.
--> SELECT ENAME, SAL, DEPTNO
    FROM EMP
    WHERE SAL IN ( SELECT MAX(SAL)
                   FROM EMP
                   WHERE DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO 
                                     FROM DEPT
                                     WHERE LOC = 'CHICAGO')
                   GROUP BY DEPTNO );

5. WAQTD dept details of empls earning sal > 2900 and from dallas.
--> SELECT *
    FROM DEPT
    WHERE LOC = 'DALLAS' AND
          DEPTNO IN ( SELECT DEPTNO 
                      FROM EMP
                      WHERE SAL > 2900);


